**Visual Prompt Studio Phase 1.1**
**Prompt** Create a large scale watercolor mural located on the side of a city building. The mural should serve as a social protest aboutenvironmental destruction. The art work should portray the message of inspiring public discussion, raising awareness, and encouraging community action to protect the planet. The subject matter includes a split image of the earth; One side with vibrant colors and full of life with oceans, fofrests, and wildlife, while the other side is full of polluted factories, wildfires,and  melting ice. Include people people of all ages reaching towards the healthy side symbolizing hope.
**Vocab Breakdown** Medium is the tools and materials used to make the artwork. The meaning is the main message. Subject matter is the visual representation and the meaning of it. The representational art is the way in which viewers can see the figures and shapes.
